      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Compound <b>D</b> is isomeric with compound <b>C</b> (Problem 13.61) and has the following <sup>13</sup>C NMR spectral data. Propose a structure.</p>\n<p><b>Compound D</b></p>\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:none\">\n<li>Broadband-decoupled <sup>13</sup>C NMR: 9.7, 29.9, 74.4, 114.4, 141.4 <i>δ</i></li>\n<li>DEPT-90: 74.4, 141.4 <i>δ</i></li>\n<li>DEPT-135: positive peaks at 9.7, 74.4, 141.4 <i>δ;</i> negative peaks at 29.9, 114.4 <i>δ</i></li>\n</ul>",
